ge body of sociological work on the state, civil society, and ethnicity to present an overview of the construction and deconstruction of the secular-Zionist national identity. He shows how Israeliness is becoming a prefix for other identities as well as a legal and political concept of citizen rights granted by the state, though not necessarily equally to different segments of society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aIsraelis. 0aJewszIsraelxIdentity. 0aNational characteristics, Israeli. 0aReligion and statezIsrael. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  acitizen rights.  across cultural.  acultural history.  ademographic study.  aethnicities.  ahistorians.  aisrael.  aisraeli military.  aisraeli society.  aisraeli state.  ajudaism.  amiddle east.  amodern history.  amulticultural society.  anational identity.  anationalism.  anonfiction.  apolitical analysts.  apolitical science.  apolitical.  aresource distribution.  asecular zionists.  asocial scientists.  asocial studies.  asociological study.  asociologists.  athought provoking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022968640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093930140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520939301/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY